  "description": "<i>High Heat Major League Baseball 2003</i> is based closely on the <a href=\"https://www.mobygames.com/game/gameboy-advance/high-heat-major-league-baseball-2002_\">previous year's version</a>, with all the same game modes and options, some changes in graphics and some other additions.<br><br>All previous game modes return: Exhibition, Season (16, 81 or 162 games), Playoffs, Home Run Derby and Practice. Season progress is again saved to battery-backed RAM. Multiplayer has been added with two-player matchups via link cable. Teams, players and stats have been updated for the new MLB season.<br><br>Gameplay is also largely unchanged. Batting and pitching are again done from a view behind the batter, but with the batter now rendered in real-time via polygons. The pitching interface via the pitching cursor is unchanged, as are the isometric field graphics. Some advanced playing techniques have been added: it is now possible to steal bases and throw bean balls.",
